# 9. あの時の気持ちも

Emu: You're thinking about leaving the Wonder Stage...?
Shiratori: Yes. I'm sorry, I know this is probably coming as a huge shock...
Emu: No, don't mind me! Umm... But can you begin by telling me why?
Shiratori: Because... I have a dream that I want to fulfill.
Shiratori: I decided to join this troupe because I admired Wonderlands×Showtime so much... But while performing here, I began to think...
Shiratori: I want to make more people smile...!
Emu: Make more people smile...?
Shiratori: Yes... I thought about this for a really long time. I love the Wonder Stage very much. But...
Shiratori: I also want to make my dream come true. So...
Shiratori: That's why...!
Emu: Oh...
Rui: I'll go and do my best.
Emu: *Nod* Okay...
Shiratori: What...?
Emu: The guests who come to the Wonder Stage really love your acting, so I'm sure you'll be able to make lots and lots of people smile...!
Emu: So...
Emu: Break a leg. I'll be rooting for you...!
Shiratori: Ms. Otori...
Shiratori: Thank you! I'll do my best...!
Emu: ...
Emu: (No, this is the right answer...)
Emu: (This is...)
???: How are you? You can tell us if something's bothering you, okay?
???: Um, Emu... You don't have to make yourself smile if something is making you feel sad!
Emu: Huh...?
Emu: (Who said those things just now...?)
Emu: Wait, what...?! It's already this late?! The meeting's gonna start soon!
Emu: I have to go get those papers about the lights, find the right meeting room and... No, there's so much I need to do!
Shosuke: These attendance figures aren't bad.
Keisuke: Yes, since we held quite a few events last month. We're experiencing a nice influx at the moment, but we'll see how the rest of this month pans out without anything special going on...
Keisuke: We'll want to look at the numbers and trends for each area while we're at it.
Shosuke: Right. I'll make sure to get a hold of them.
Keisuke: If there's nothing else to report, then I think we can call it a day...
Shosuke: I have nothing else to add. What about you, Emu?
Emu: U-Uhh...
Emu: There is something I wanna discuss with you guys.
Keisuke: I see. Shiratori wants to leave...
Emu: *Nod* He's gonna leave the Wonder Stage in order to go make his dream come true. So...
Emu: We're probably gonna have to start holding auditions to find a new troupe member to fill his spot.
Emu: He won't actually be leaving for a little while, but I think we should come up with a schedule now before—
Shosuke: Stop right there.
Shosuke: Does this mean you already agreed to let him go...?
Emu: Huh? Yeah, I did...
Shosuke: You're joking, right...?
Keisuke: ...
Keisuke: Now I see...
Keisuke: What you did may've been in Shiratori's best interest...
Keisuke: But you definitely made a serious administrative mistake.
Emu: What...?
Keisuke: Setting aside whether or not he would've accepted any counteroffers, he's a valued asset. So, your first move should've been to stop him.
Keisuke: Given that you had a chance to do so...
Shosuke: I mean, at this point, Shiratori's the face of the Wonder Stage.
Shosuke: I don't even want to begin thinking about how the guests are going to react when they hear the news.
Emu: Oh...
Emu: Yeah, you guys are right...
Keisuke: As your brother, I'd like to ask...
Keisuke: Did it ever cross your mind to get him to stay?
Emu: Did it ever cross my mind...?
Emu: It was sad to hear, but I wanted to show him my support...
Emu: I mean, Shiratori's such a dazzling actor. You can't help but smile when you see him perform...
Emu: So, I want him to make his dream come true and put smiles on the faces of even more people...
Keisuke: Is that all...?
Emu: Huh?
Keisuke: I understand wanting to respect his dreams and wishes. But...
Keisuke: Lately, I feel that you've been doing everything in your power to suppress your own feelings...
Keisuke: In particular, when it comes to people leaving.
Keisuke: And this all started... Around the time the other members of Wonderlands×Showtime left, I want to say.
Emu: ...
Emu: I wanted us to keep going...
Emu: I wanted to keep seeing people smile from the Wonder Stage together...
Emu: But... But...!
Emu: If I stopped them, and that prevented their dreams from coming true...
Shosuke: Emu...
Keisuke: It's okay for you to be a little more honest about how you feel...
Keisuke: So, if you're feeling sad, then you should say that you're sad.
Keisuke: To us... And your friends.
Emu: But...
Keisuke: Yes, there's bound to come a day when the nature of your position demands that you not waver. But, for now...
Keisuke: You should stop turning a blind eye and suppressing your feelings if it means forcing yourself...
Emu: A-Are you sure...?
Emu: I want to help people make their dreams come true... I don't want to get in their way...
Shosuke: I can't say there's anything wrong with that, but... It's perfectly normal for you to feel sad.
Shosuke: After all, they're your friends, and you put on shows with them.
Emu: (Right. It's perfectly normal to feel this way...)
Emu: (To feel sad and want to do shows with them again...)
Emu: (I thought I had to not say what I was feeling so I wouldn't get in their way...)
Emu: (But these feelings that are still lingering inside me...)
Emu: (It's okay for me to hold on to them.)
Emu: (Including the tightness I felt in my chest that time...)
Emu: *Nod* Thanks, you guys...
Keisuke: Anyway, let's call it a day here. I'm sure you still have some things you need to do.
Emu: Huh?
Keisuke: Aren't you throwing that farewell party with Wonderlands×Showtime?
Emu: N-N-N-No, I forgot! I still have a ton left to do for that!
Shosuke: What's there to do? They're just coming to visit the park, right?
Emu: I have to make special farewell party guidebooks for us! And I still haven't decided how I want them to look...
Emu: I'm gonna head back to my room! Good night, Keisuke, Shosuke!
Keisuke: Okay, good night.
Shosuke: What did she mean, “farewell party guidebooks”...?
Emu: Yes, I'm the first one here♪
Emu: (Hehe. I'm glad I was able to finish making those guidebooks.)
Emu: (I'm calling this plan “Operation: Let's Go See Shows At All The Stages☆”)
Emu: (It's got all the shows I recommend seeing when you're at Phoenix Wonderland, and tons of trivia!)
Emu: (I really hope they like them.)
Staff Member: Oh, Ms. Otori, there you are...!
Emu: (Doesn't he work at the Wonder Stage?)
Emu: Umm... Is something the matter?
Staff Member: I'm sorry, I know this is your day off... But we've run into a bit of trouble.
Staff Member: The thing is, the cast is trying to fly back from their traveling performance, but they're currently stuck at the airport due to inclement weather.
Staff Member: If nothing improves, they're not going to make it back in time for today's afternoon showing!
Emu: What...?
